WEBVTT

00:06.887 --> 00:10.721
Meredith: WHEN I WAS 5,
MY MOM LOST ME IN A PARK.

00:10.721 --> 00:14.435
I DON'T REMEMBER MUCH,
EXCEPT THAT ONE MINUTE,

00:14.435 --> 00:18.269
I WAS RIDING THE CAROUSEL,
AND THE NEXT...

00:18.269 --> 00:19.730
SHE WAS GONE.

00:19.730 --> 00:21.312
I'LL BE HOME
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

00:21.312 --> 00:23.444
IT'S GOOD.
IT'S TIME.

00:23.444 --> 00:26.317
Meredith: I DON'T KNOW, I JUST
FEEL LIKE I JUST GOT YOU BACK

00:26.317 --> 00:29.029
AND NOW WE'RE GOING AGAIN
AND I-I JUST HAVE TO STAY HERE.

00:29.029 --> 00:30.241
YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU DO.

00:30.241 --> 00:32.323
YOU HAVE TO STAY HERE.

00:32.323 --> 00:33.914
STAY HERE.
DON'T MOVE.

00:33.914 --> 00:34.915
DON'T MOVE.

00:34.915 --> 00:36.036
WAIT FOR ME.

00:36.036 --> 00:37.037
WAIT FOR ME.

00:37.037 --> 00:38.329
I DON'T REMEMBER
HOW I FOUND HER.

00:38.329 --> 00:39.830
Ellis: RICHARD!

00:39.830 --> 00:42.293
I DON'T REMEMBER
HOW I GOT HOME.

00:42.293 --> 00:43.714
[ ELLIS CRYING ]
ARE YOU OKAY?

00:43.714 --> 00:47.758
ALL I REMEMBER
IS WHAT HAPPENED NEXT.

00:47.758 --> 00:49.470
SHE TOLD ME NOT TO WORRY.

00:49.470 --> 00:52.133
SHE TOLD ME
EVERYTHING WOULD BE FINE.

00:52.133 --> 00:54.305
I'LL BE BACK
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT.

00:54.305 --> 00:57.638
FUNNY, ISN'T IT,
THE WAY MEMORY WORKS?

00:57.638 --> 00:59.850
THE THINGS
YOU CAN'T QUITE REMEMBER...

00:59.850 --> 01:02.523
AND THE THINGS
YOU CAN NEVER FORGET.

01:02.523 --> 01:05.736
[ Echoing ] THE CAROUSEL
NEVER STOPS TURNING.

01:08.859 --> 01:12.493
[ HOUNDMOUTH'S "SEDONA" PLAYS ]

01:18.829 --> 01:20.871
[ BUZZING ]

01:23.624 --> 01:25.166
[ WHIMPERS ]

01:25.166 --> 01:27.298
OKAY, ZO-ZO, WALK A LITTLE
FASTER 'CAUSE WE ARE LATE.

01:27.298 --> 01:29.130
AND WHO
CAN NEVER BE LATE?

01:29.130 --> 01:30.171
SURGEONS.

01:30.171 --> 01:31.712
WHAT HAPPENS
IF SURGEONS ARE LATE?

01:31.712 --> 01:32.843
PEOPLE DIE?

01:32.843 --> 01:34.014
RIGHT ON, SISTER.

01:35.516 --> 01:37.138
HEY, IT'S ME.

01:37.138 --> 01:39.220
I'M ON THE FERRY.

01:39.220 --> 01:42.563
I-I JUST WANTED
TO SAY THAT, UM...

01:42.563 --> 01:45.105
♪ SEDONA ARABELLA ♪

01:47.988 --> 01:49.690
[ HORNS BLARING ]

01:51.822 --> 01:55.156
♪ WHEN JOHN FORD SAID
WON'T YOU HOP ON IN ♪

01:55.156 --> 01:58.499
♪ AND THE STAGECOACH, BABY,
GONNA TAKE YOU FOR A SPIN ♪

01:58.499 --> 02:00.701
♪ OH, OH ♪

02:00.701 --> 02:03.003
♪ OH, OH ♪

02:06.247 --> 02:08.008
YOU'RE NEVER GONNA MAKE
YOUR FLIGHT.

02:08.008 --> 02:09.049
DEREK:
I'll make it.

02:09.049 --> 02:10.671
Miranda: NO, YOU WON'T.
YOU'RE GONNA MISS YOUR FLIGHT.

02:10.671 --> 02:13.214
WHO'S THAT?
BAILEY?

02:13.214 --> 02:14.465
I'M NOT
GONNA MISS MY FLIGHT.

02:14.465 --> 02:17.017
THERE WAS A HUGE ACCIDENT ON
THE 5. ALL THE LANES ARE CLOSED.

02:17.017 --> 02:18.429
THE TRAFFIC
IS INSANE.

02:18.429 --> 02:20.681
NOW, WHY DOES KEPNER MAKE THAT
SOUND LIKE IT'S A GOOD THING?

02:20.681 --> 02:22.643
AMELIA: We have a guy
from the accident on our table.

02:22.643 --> 02:24.725
Bailey and Kepner are sewing up
all the holes in his gut.

02:24.725 --> 02:26.527
I AM REPAIRING
THE UN-REPAIRABLE.

02:26.527 --> 02:28.028
I AM
OUT-OF-CONTROL AMAZING.

02:28.028 --> 02:30.271
Miranda: NO, I AM
OUT-OF-CONTROL AMAZING.

02:30.271 --> 02:33.073
YOU ARE A GUEST
IN MY GUTS. HUSH.

02:33.073 --> 02:34.945
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:34.945 --> 02:37.198
THE POINT IS YOU MIGHT AS
WELL TURN AROUND NOW 'CAUSE
YOU'LL MISS YOUR FLIGHT.

02:37.198 --> 02:38.449
DEREK: I'm not
gonna miss my flight.

02:38.449 --> 02:40.120
I HAVE A SECRET SHORTCUT.

02:40.120 --> 02:41.872
Both: THERE ARE NOT SHORTCUTS
TO THE AIRPORT.

02:41.872 --> 02:43.204
THAT YOU KNOW ABOUT.

02:43.204 --> 02:45.165
COME ON. I'M DOING
A SPONDYLOLISTHESIS TODAY.

02:45.165 --> 02:48.048
I'M SAYING IF YOU HEAD BACK NOW,
I MIGHT LET YOU --

02:48.048 --> 02:50.000
I'M GONNA LOSE YOU HERE
IN A SECOND.

02:50.000 --> 02:51.212
CELLPHONE RECEPTION'S BAD.

02:51.212 --> 02:53.674
DEREK, ARE YOU STILL THERE?
I CAN'T HEAR YOU.

02:53.674 --> 02:55.426
NO, I SAID I'M GONNA LOSE
THE CELLPHONE RECEPTION.

02:55.426 --> 02:56.677
IT'S BAD HERE.

02:56.677 --> 02:58.058
[ STATIC ]
AMY?

02:58.058 --> 02:59.059
DEREK? DEREK?

02:59.059 --> 03:00.851
Amy,
are you there?

03:00.851 --> 03:02.062
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

03:02.062 --> 03:03.974
LOST HIM.

03:03.974 --> 03:05.516
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

03:05.516 --> 03:07.308
♪ I GUESS THAT'S BETTER
THAN A GRAVE AND A HEARSE ♪

03:07.308 --> 03:09.019
♪ OH, OH ♪

03:10.571 --> 03:14.235
♪ OH, OH ♪

03:14.235 --> 03:15.406
[ ENGINE REVS ]

03:15.406 --> 03:17.818
I'M DOING 10 MILES
OVER THE SPEED LIMIT.

03:17.818 --> 03:19.990
THAT'S NOT FAST ENOUGH
FOR YOU? GEE.

03:19.990 --> 03:22.032
♪ YOU'RE NOT FORGOTTEN ♪

03:22.032 --> 03:25.376
♪ YOU GOT THE CASH
BUT YOUR CREDIT'S NO GOOD ♪

03:25.376 --> 03:29.460
♪ YOU FLIPPED THE SCRIPT
AND SHOT THE PLOT ♪

03:29.460 --> 03:31.091
♪ I REMEMBER,
I REMEMBER WHEN YOUR NEON ♪

03:31.091 --> 03:35.836
♪ USED TO BURN
SO BRIGHT AND PINK ♪

03:37.217 --> 03:39.390
♪ A SATURDAY NIGHT
KIND OF PINK ♪

03:39.390 --> 03:41.221
[ SIGHS ]

03:41.221 --> 03:42.843
[ TIRES SQUEAL ]

03:45.686 --> 03:47.187
[ TIRES SCREECHING ]

03:50.771 --> 03:52.112
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

04:11.081 --> 04:12.212
[ GRUNTS ]

04:12.212 --> 04:15.045
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

04:17.338 --> 04:19.800
WHERE'S MY PH-- PHONE?

04:30.891 --> 04:33.063
HEY.
MA'AM. MA'AM.

04:33.063 --> 04:34.655
MY NAME'S DEREK.

04:34.655 --> 04:36.066
ARE YOU OKAY?

04:36.066 --> 04:38.899
WINNIE!

04:41.862 --> 04:42.663
WINNIE!

04:42.663 --> 04:43.954
WINNIE! WINNIE!

04:43.954 --> 04:45.956
HEY,
I CAN'T OPEN THE DOOR.
WINNIE!

04:45.956 --> 04:47.868
MA'AM. HEY.
WINNIE! WINNIE!

04:47.868 --> 04:49.330
HEY.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

04:49.330 --> 04:51.462
SARAH.
SARAH,
WHO'S WINNIE?

04:51.462 --> 04:53.834
MY -- MY DAUGHTER.
SHE'S, UH, SHE'S IN THE BACK.

04:53.834 --> 04:55.215
SHE'S NOT ANSWERING,
AND I DON'T KNOW IF SHE'S OKAY.

04:55.215 --> 04:56.337
SARAH.

04:56.337 --> 04:58.218
SARAH, I NEED YOU
TO STAY CALM, OKAY?

04:58.218 --> 04:59.129
DEEP BREATHS.
GOOD.

04:59.129 --> 05:00.721
STAY CALM.
I'M GONNA BE RIGHT BACK, OKAY?

05:00.721 --> 05:02.182
MM-HMM.
TRY NOT TO MOVE.

05:02.182 --> 05:03.554
OKAY.

05:03.554 --> 05:06.056
HEY.
YOU WINNIE?

05:06.056 --> 05:08.479
IS ANYTHING HURT,
LIKE YOUR NECK OR...?

05:09.980 --> 05:11.231
IS THAT
WHY YOU CAN'T TALK?

05:12.312 --> 05:15.816
I THINK
I'M DEAD.

05:15.816 --> 05:17.778
AM I DEAD?

05:17.778 --> 05:20.200
LET ME FEEL
YOUR WRIST.

05:24.074 --> 05:25.536
WELL,
YOU'RE NOT DEAD.

05:25.536 --> 05:27.037
I CAN FEEL A PULSE
IN YOUR WRIST.

05:27.037 --> 05:28.328
YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?

05:28.328 --> 05:29.660
WHAT?

05:29.660 --> 05:31.041
IT MEANS
YOUR HEART'S STILL BEATING.

05:31.041 --> 05:33.083
AND YOU CAN'T BE DEAD
IF YOUR HEART'S STILL BEATING.

05:33.083 --> 05:35.045
YOU SEE,
I'M A DOCTOR,

05:35.045 --> 05:37.007
AND I'M TELLING YOU IF YOU EVER
WANT TO KNOW YOU'RE DEAD,

05:37.007 --> 05:38.258
FEEL YOUR PULSE.

05:42.843 --> 05:45.015
I CAN FEEL IT.

05:47.057 --> 05:48.098
I'M NOT DEAD.

05:48.098 --> 05:49.059
YOU'RE NOT DEAD.

05:49.059 --> 05:50.230
I'M NOT DEAD,
MOMMY!

05:50.230 --> 05:51.892
Sarah:
SHE'S OKAY?!

05:51.892 --> 05:53.273
OKAY,
SHE'S FINE.

05:53.273 --> 05:55.065
DO YOU HAVE A CELLPHONE IN
THERE? I NEED TO CALL FOR HELP.

05:55.065 --> 05:57.107
UH, UH, YEAH.
I SEE IT.

05:57.107 --> 05:59.480
IT SHATTERED, THOUGH.
IT -- IT WOULDN'T MATTER,ANYWAY.

05:59.480 --> 06:01.191
I DRIVE THIS ROAD
EVERY WEEK,

06:01.191 --> 06:02.823
AND THERE'S NEVER
ANY CELL SIGNAL.

06:02.823 --> 06:04.244
OKAY, I'M GONNA CHECK
ON THE OTHER DRIVER,

06:04.244 --> 06:05.986
SEE IF THEY HAVE A PHONE.
YOU'RE LEAVING US?

06:05.986 --> 06:07.828
WHAT? NO. I JUST SAID THERE'S
NEVER ANY CELL SIGNAL UP HERE.

06:07.828 --> 06:09.159
IT'S NOT
GONNA BE DIFFERENT.

06:09.159 --> 06:10.581
SARAH,
I'M GONNA CHECK ON THEM...

06:10.581 --> 06:12.162
I CAN'T -- I CAN'T MOVE.
I AM STUCK.

06:12.162 --> 06:13.834
...LIKE I CHECKED ON YOU, OKAY?
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
PLEASE DON'T LEAVE.

06:13.834 --> 06:15.996
YOU PROMISE?

06:15.996 --> 06:17.087
I PROMISE.

06:17.087 --> 06:18.208
OKAY.

06:25.426 --> 06:27.007
HELLO?

06:27.007 --> 06:28.719
[ GRUNTS ] HELLO?

06:30.971 --> 06:33.223
HELLO?

06:35.015 --> 06:36.937
Alana: HELP!

06:36.937 --> 06:38.859
[ GASPING ]

06:38.859 --> 06:41.902
[ WHIMPERING ]

06:41.902 --> 06:43.403
HELP!

06:43.403 --> 06:45.195
HELP!
[ WHIMPERING ]

06:45.195 --> 06:46.326
HEY.

06:46.326 --> 06:47.908
CAN YOU
TELL ME YOUR NAME?

06:47.908 --> 06:48.909
ALANA.
ALANA.

06:48.909 --> 06:49.990
IT'S HARD
TO BREATHE.

06:49.990 --> 06:50.991
OKAY.

06:50.991 --> 06:53.163
ALL RIGHT.
LET'S TAKE A SECOND.

06:53.163 --> 06:54.995
YOU PROBABLY GOT THE WIND
KNOCKED OUT OF YOU WHEN
YOU HIT THE GROUND.

06:54.995 --> 06:57.998
LUCKY YOU DIDN'T HIT
THE PAVEMENT.

06:57.998 --> 07:00.210
YEAH.
YOU FEEL ANY PAIN?

07:00.210 --> 07:01.882
I DON'T --
I DON'T THINK SO.

07:01.882 --> 07:02.883
DOES IT HURT ANYWHERE?

07:02.883 --> 07:04.044
NO.

07:04.044 --> 07:05.756
I'M NOT
SUPPOSED TO BE HERE.

07:05.756 --> 07:07.427
I HAVE TO GO.

07:07.427 --> 07:09.389
I-I HAVE TO GO.
I HAVE TO GO.
CAREFUL. CAREFUL.

07:09.389 --> 07:11.431
I HAVE TO CALL MY MOM.
WHERE'S MY PHONE?

07:11.431 --> 07:13.644
MY PHONE'S NOT WORKING.
WHY IS MY PHONE NOT WORKING?

07:13.644 --> 07:15.225
OKAY.
LISTEN TO ME.

07:15.225 --> 07:17.107
LISTEN TO ME.
YOU'RE PROBABLY IN SHOCK, OKAY?

07:17.107 --> 07:18.649
YOU HAVE A LOT OF ADRENALINE
GOING THROUGH YOU RIGHT NOW.

07:18.649 --> 07:21.021
THERE MIGHT BE
SOMETHING WRONG WITH YOU

07:21.021 --> 07:23.984
THAT YOU DON'T FEEL RIGHT NOW,
SO I NEED YOU TO SLOW DOWN.

07:23.984 --> 07:25.195
OKAY.

07:25.195 --> 07:26.987
ALL RIGHT.

07:26.987 --> 07:28.829
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT DAY IT IS?

07:28.829 --> 07:31.281
THURSDAY.
I'M SUPPOSED TO BE AT SCHOOL.

07:31.281 --> 07:32.993
IN CHEM.
WE HAVE A QUIZ.

07:32.993 --> 07:34.995
IS THAT
WHY YOU WERE DRIVING SO CRAZY?

07:34.995 --> 07:36.036
I WASN'T DRIVING.

07:36.036 --> 07:37.998
WHO WAS DRIVING?

07:37.998 --> 07:40.130
CHARLIE.
IT'S HIS DAD'S CAR.

08:00.150 --> 08:02.903
HEY!
HEY, CHARLIE.

08:03.984 --> 08:05.485
HEY.

08:05.485 --> 08:07.237
STOP.

08:07.237 --> 08:10.661
STOP.

08:10.661 --> 08:12.492
YOU OKAY?

08:12.492 --> 08:14.074
YEAH.
I'M FINE.

08:14.074 --> 08:17.037
HEY, LET'S GET
OUT OF THE ROAD.

08:18.288 --> 08:20.250
I DON'T FEEL GOOD.

08:20.250 --> 08:21.712
W-WHAT HAPPENED?
YOU WERE
IN AN ACCIDENT.

08:21.712 --> 08:23.043
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

08:23.043 --> 08:24.795
HEY,
W-WHAT HAPPENED?

08:24.795 --> 08:26.466
UM, LET'S GET YOU
OUT OF THIS ROAD.
I REALLY DON'T FEEL SO GOOD.

08:26.466 --> 08:28.629
WHAT HAPPENED?
UM, LET'S GET
OUT OF THE ROAD.

08:28.629 --> 08:30.891
SIR, D-DO YOU KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED?
YEAH, YOU --

08:30.891 --> 08:32.392
'CAUSE I REALLY
DON'T FEEL SO GOOD.

08:32.392 --> 08:34.264
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
WHAT -- WHAT HAPPENED?

08:34.264 --> 08:37.598
CHARLIE, I DON'T KNOW WHAT
HAPPENED, CHARLIE. I DON'T...

08:42.943 --> 08:44.144
OH, MY GOD, CHARLIE.
LOOK AT YOUR HEAD.

08:44.144 --> 08:45.145
ARE YOU OKAY?

08:45.145 --> 08:46.857
HELP ME
GET HIM DOWN.

08:46.857 --> 08:48.198
Alana:
WHAT'S WRONG WITH HIM?

08:48.198 --> 08:50.110
WHY ISN'T HE SAYING ANYTHING?
CHARLIE?

08:50.110 --> 08:52.783
HE HIT HIS HEAD REALLY HARD.
I NEED TO FIND A FIRST-AID KIT.

08:58.789 --> 09:01.001
OH, YOU GOT
TO BE KIDDING ME.

09:07.377 --> 09:09.339
OKAY, ARE YOU -- YOU GUYS
STILL DOING OKAY IN HERE?

09:09.339 --> 09:10.671
Winnie: YEAH.
YOU'RE GONNA
GET US OUT NOW?

09:10.671 --> 09:11.842
I NEED SUPPLIES.
WHAT DO YOU GOT IN THE BACK?

09:11.842 --> 09:14.885
UM, A FIRST-AID KIT --
WINNIE'S BACKPACK.

09:16.977 --> 09:19.229
OKAY, WINNIE, IT'S SAFETY GLASS.
IT'S NOT GONNA HURT YOU,

09:19.229 --> 09:21.231
BUT I NEED YOU
TO GET BACK, ALL RIGHT?

09:21.231 --> 09:23.183
GET BACK.

09:30.150 --> 09:31.451
ARE YOU GONNA
LEAVE US HERE AGAIN?

09:31.451 --> 09:33.784
[ SIGHS ] NO.

09:34.995 --> 09:36.036
THINK YOU CAN
CLIMB OUT FOR ME?

09:36.036 --> 09:37.327
YEAH, I CAN.
Sarah: BE CAREFUL.

09:37.327 --> 09:39.369
CAN YOU MAKE SURE
WINNIE'S CAREFUL?
OKAY, I GOT HER.

09:39.369 --> 09:42.162
IS SHE OUT?
YEAH, SHE'S OUT.

09:43.874 --> 09:44.875
I'M OUT,
MOM.

09:44.875 --> 09:46.006
I'M GOOD.
OKAY.

09:46.006 --> 09:47.467
ALL RIGHT, SARAH,
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

09:47.467 --> 09:48.879
NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

09:50.210 --> 09:51.421
I'M GONNA GET
YOUR MOM.

09:51.421 --> 09:53.133
WINNIE, YOU THINK
YOU CAN GO DOWN THERE

09:53.133 --> 09:54.554
AND KEEP
THOSE TWO COMPANY?

09:54.554 --> 09:57.267
THE PEOPLE WHO HIT OUR CAR?
NO, THANKS.

09:57.267 --> 09:59.019
I'M GOOD
TO WAIT HERE.

09:59.019 --> 10:01.481
THERE'S BANDAGES IN HERE.
THEY COULD USE THEM.

10:01.481 --> 10:03.854
MY MOM'S GONNA BE
IN A LOT OF PAIN,

10:03.854 --> 10:06.026
AND YOU DON'T WANT ME
TO SEE IT.

10:07.067 --> 10:08.729
NO.

10:09.780 --> 10:11.782
YES.

10:11.782 --> 10:14.194
I CAN DEAL
WITH SEEING STUFF.

10:14.194 --> 10:16.997
MY DAD DIED
RIGHT IN FRONT OF ME.

10:16.997 --> 10:19.039
WE WERE FISHING
ON THE LAKE,

10:19.039 --> 10:22.082
AND HE HAD A HEART ATTACK
ON THE BOAT AND DIED.

10:23.543 --> 10:25.165
DO YOU FISH?

10:25.165 --> 10:28.628
NO ONE'S GONNA DIE,
WINNIE.

10:28.628 --> 10:33.513
YOU AREN'T GOD, SO...
YOU DON'T KNOW.

10:36.596 --> 10:39.389
I'LL GO WAIT
WITH THEM.

10:43.563 --> 10:46.066
OKAY, SARAH,
YOU READY?

10:46.066 --> 10:48.108
ONE, TWO, THREE.

10:58.408 --> 11:03.043
[ SIGHS ] GOD,
I LOVED THIS CAR SO MUCH!

11:03.043 --> 11:05.706
IT'S THE FIRST NEW CAR
THAT WE EVER HAD.

11:05.706 --> 11:08.999
AND...BOOM, SOME RICH GUY IN
AN OVERPRICED MIDLIFE CRISIS

11:08.999 --> 11:10.590
JUST --
YOU SAW HIM, RIGHT?

11:10.590 --> 11:12.592
THE GUY
THAT HIT US?

11:12.592 --> 11:13.673
TOTAL PIG, RIGHT?

11:13.673 --> 11:15.345
IT WAS
A 17-YEAR-OLD KID.

11:16.426 --> 11:19.429
CRAP.
NOW I CAN'T EVEN HATE HIM.

11:20.851 --> 11:23.103
[ GASPS ] I BET
HIS PARENTS ARE AWFUL.

11:23.103 --> 11:24.644
ALL RIGHT, SARAH, I GOT
TO GET YOU OUT OF THIS CAR.

11:24.644 --> 11:26.016
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

11:26.016 --> 11:27.647
LISTEN. GETTING YOU OUT?
IT'S GOING TO HURT. A LOT.

11:27.647 --> 11:30.440
OKAY. I KNOW
THAT I SHOULD BE IN PAIN,

11:30.440 --> 11:33.613
AND, UM, I DON'T KNOW
I-IF IT'S SHOCK

11:33.613 --> 11:36.817
OR IF IT'S THAT
MY LEG HURTS SO BADLY

11:36.817 --> 11:38.779
THAT I ALMOST
CAN'T RECOGNIZE IT.

11:38.779 --> 11:42.082
ALMOST FEELS NORMAL, SO MAYBE IT
WON'T BE SO BAD GETTING ME OUT.

11:42.082 --> 11:45.085
SOUNDS LIKE
YOU DISLOCATED YOUR HIP.

11:45.085 --> 11:47.087
WHICH MEANS I GOT
TO GET YOU OUT OF THIS CAR.

11:47.087 --> 11:48.458
OHH! OKAY.

11:48.458 --> 11:50.330
DOWN ON THE GROUND, AND THEN
POP IT BACK IN THE SOCKET.

11:50.330 --> 11:53.043
OKAY. ALL RIGHT.
ALL RIGHT, I'M NOT
GONNA SUGARCOAT IT.

11:53.043 --> 11:54.044
IT'S GONNA BE HORRIBLE.

11:54.044 --> 11:55.675
[ GROANS ]

11:55.675 --> 11:57.007
WHAT HAPPENED?

11:57.007 --> 11:59.509
THERE WAS
AN ACCIDENT.

11:59.509 --> 12:01.181
WHAT HAPPENED?

12:01.181 --> 12:02.973
THERE WAS A CAR ACCIDENT,
CHARLIE. [ GROANS ] OW!

12:02.973 --> 12:05.225
ARE YOU OKAY?

12:05.225 --> 12:08.228
MY STOMACH HURTS.
REALLY BAD.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.900
I THINK I'M GONNA THROW UP
OR SOMETHING.

12:10.771 --> 12:11.812
WHERE ARE WE?

12:11.812 --> 12:14.564
WE HAD A CAR ACCIDENT,
OKAY?!

12:14.564 --> 12:16.026
WE HAD
AN ACCIDENT!

12:16.026 --> 12:18.909
[ SARAH SCREAMING ]

12:18.909 --> 12:20.620
OKAY, STOP.
PLEASE, STOP.
I NEED
TO FIX YOUR LEG.

12:20.620 --> 12:22.162
NO,
LET'S WAIT.

12:22.162 --> 12:24.204
LET'S WAIT, UH, FOR HELP 'CAUSE
HELP'S COMING. IT'S COMING.

12:24.204 --> 12:26.576
SARAH, THE DISLOCATION
HAS CUT OFF THE BLOOD
SUPPLY TO YOUR LEG.

12:26.576 --> 12:28.288
IF I DON'T DO SOMETHING,
YOU COULD LOSE IT.

12:28.288 --> 12:30.170
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT,
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.

12:30.170 --> 12:31.171
PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE.

12:31.171 --> 12:32.372
OKAY.

12:32.372 --> 12:33.583
[ CRACK ]
AAH!

12:33.583 --> 12:35.375
OHH!
GOOD.

12:35.375 --> 12:37.798
OHH.
THANK GOD.

12:37.798 --> 12:40.220
IT'S GOOD.
I HATE YOU.

12:40.220 --> 12:41.972
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:41.972 --> 12:43.844
DEREK! CHARLIE'S CAR!
THE CAR'S ON FIRE!

12:45.595 --> 12:47.097
HEY!

12:48.558 --> 12:49.940
ALANA, RUN!
WHAT ABOUT CHARLIE?

12:49.940 --> 12:51.021
GET AWAY
FROM THE CAR!

12:51.021 --> 12:52.312
COME ON, CHARLIE,
YOU GOT TO GET UP.

12:52.312 --> 12:55.275
GET UP, GET UP,
GET UP, GET UP. COME ON.
AAH! AAH!

12:55.275 --> 12:57.067
[ GRUNTS ]

12:57.067 --> 12:58.819
COME ON.

13:03.403 --> 13:05.205
OH, MY GOD!

13:13.623 --> 13:15.085
THAT EXPLOSION
WAS HUGE.

13:15.085 --> 13:16.126
Derek: DO YOU SEE
ALL THAT SMOKE?

13:16.126 --> 13:17.257
SOMEONE'S GONNA SEE IT,

13:17.257 --> 13:18.588
AND THEN THAT SOMEONE
IS GONNA SEND SOME HELP.

13:18.588 --> 13:19.840
IT'S LIKE
A SMOKE SIGNAL.

13:19.840 --> 13:21.511
MM-HMM.
WE'RE SO RESCUED.

13:22.722 --> 13:24.014
I'M NOT
SUPPOSED TO BE HERE.

13:24.014 --> 13:25.976
OKAY, WE JUST NEED TO HANG ON
FOR A LITTLE BIT LONGER.

13:25.976 --> 13:27.888
IS EVERYBODY OKAY?
I'M NOT
SUPPOSED TO BE HERE.

13:27.888 --> 13:30.480
I'M A MATHLETE.
I TAKE FIVE A.P. CLASSES.

13:30.480 --> 13:32.232
I'M FIRST CHAIR
ON CELLO.

13:32.232 --> 13:34.644
I HAVE
A PERFECT ATTENDANCE RECORD.

13:34.644 --> 13:37.277
I HAVEN'T MISSED ONE DAY --
NOT ONE DAY OF SCHOOL.

13:37.277 --> 13:38.398
I'M BORING.

13:38.398 --> 13:41.111
[ CHUCKLES ]
CHARLIE ABBOT'S PROM KING.

13:41.111 --> 13:43.153
[ Crying ]
HE'S IN REMEDIAL MATH.

13:43.153 --> 13:44.995
HE'S NEVER EVEN
HEARD OF A.P.

13:44.995 --> 13:47.998
HE'S DUMB AND POPULAR
AND TOTALLY GORGEOUS.

13:47.998 --> 13:50.830
AND THIS MORNING, HE SAYS, "YOU
WANT TO GO FOR A RIDE?" TO ME.

13:50.830 --> 13:54.754
SO, THE EARTH IS SHIFTING
ON ITS AXIS OR SOMETHING CRAZY

13:54.754 --> 13:56.006
BECAUSE NO WAY.

13:56.006 --> 13:58.508
CHARLIE ABBOTT
IS NOT SUPPOSED TO KISS ME.

13:58.508 --> 14:00.090
AAH! AAH!

14:00.090 --> 14:01.882
MM, SO SOMETHING IS WRONG.

14:01.882 --> 14:04.674
SOME WORMHOLE
TO ANOTHER UNIVERSE HAS OPENED.

14:04.674 --> 14:07.307
I DON'T KNOW,
BUT NOW I AM ON A ROAD

14:07.307 --> 14:09.729
BECAUSE THE CAR I WAS IN
JUST FLEW THROUGH THE AIR

14:09.729 --> 14:11.431
AND I JUST RAN
FROM A GIANT FIREBALL

14:11.431 --> 14:13.063
AND CHARLIE ABBOTT'S BRAIN
IS BROKEN

14:13.063 --> 14:14.644
AND MY STOMACH IS KILLING ME.

14:14.644 --> 14:17.237
SO I AM OBVIOUSLY
NOT SUPPOSED TO BE HERE.

14:17.237 --> 14:19.029
SO, CAN SOMEONE
PLEASE WAKE ME UP

14:19.029 --> 14:21.191
OR WAVE YOUR MAGIC WAND
OR CLICK YOUR HEELS THREE TIMES

14:21.191 --> 14:22.532
OR WHATEVER
SO I CAN GO HOME?

14:22.532 --> 14:24.404
PLEASE. PLEASE.

14:24.404 --> 14:25.906
WHAT? WHAT IS IT?
JUST LOOK AT MY EYES.

14:25.906 --> 14:27.247
WHAT'S WRONG?
LOOK AT MY FACE.
LOOK AT MY EYES, OKAY?

14:27.247 --> 14:28.288
I'M SCARED.

14:28.288 --> 14:30.951
OKAY, OKAY,
JUST LOOK AT ME.
DEREK?

14:30.951 --> 14:33.253
OKAY, WE NEED TO GET HER DOWN
ON THE GROUND. HELP ME, OKAY?

14:33.253 --> 14:35.085
JUST COME WITH ME
RIGHT NOW.
OKAY.

14:35.085 --> 14:36.296
EASY, EASY.
[ MOANING ]

14:36.296 --> 14:37.417
I JUST NEED
TO UNDO A BUTTON

14:37.417 --> 14:38.838
SO I CAN LOOK
AT YOUR STOMACH, OKAY?

14:38.838 --> 14:40.840
I'M SCARED.
I KNOW.

14:40.840 --> 14:42.963
I'M NOT GONNA GO ANYWHERE.
I'M HERE, OKAY? LOOK AT ME.

14:42.963 --> 14:45.265
LOOK AT ME.
LOOK AT ME IN THE EYES.

14:47.347 --> 14:49.009
ALL RIGHT,
I'M GONNA OPEN UP YOUR PANTS

14:49.009 --> 14:50.350
SO I CAN JUST SEE
YOUR STOMACH, OKAY?

14:50.350 --> 14:52.852
I JUST WANT
TO TAKE A QUICK LOOK.

14:55.185 --> 14:56.606
I'M GONNA TAKE A LOOK.

14:57.687 --> 14:58.979
OHH, GOD!

14:58.979 --> 15:00.520
SARAH.
DEREK.

15:00.520 --> 15:02.943
WHAT'S WRONG WITH ME?
IS IT MY STOMACH?

15:02.943 --> 15:04.574
IS IT BLEEDING?
IT'S OKAY.

15:04.574 --> 15:05.695
AM I DYING?
NO, NO, NO.

15:05.695 --> 15:07.197
I WANT TO KNOW.

15:07.197 --> 15:08.618
YOU HAVE A LITTLE CUT IN
YOUR TUMMY. IT'S GONNA BE OKAY.

15:08.618 --> 15:10.620
[ MOANS ]
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.
I CAN TAKE CARE OF IT.

15:10.620 --> 15:12.032
HOW?

15:12.032 --> 15:14.834
HOW ARE YOU
GONNA FIX IT?

15:14.834 --> 15:16.796
YOU DON'T KNOW.
[ SIGHS ]

15:16.796 --> 15:18.798
OH, MY GOD,
I'M GONNA DIE OUT HERE.

15:18.798 --> 15:20.540
CAN YOU
STOP SAYING THAT?

15:20.540 --> 15:23.003
IT'S INSULTING.
I DON'T LET PEOPLE DIE.

15:23.003 --> 15:26.046
I'M VERY GOOD
AT MY JOB,

15:26.046 --> 15:27.217
EVEN NEXT TO THE ROADSIDE,
OKAY?

15:27.217 --> 15:29.009
I'M THINKING.

15:29.009 --> 15:30.550
I'M THINKING.

15:32.552 --> 15:34.684
[ GROANS ]

15:34.684 --> 15:36.106
SARAH.

15:37.017 --> 15:39.109
YOU HAVE DRY-CLEANING
IN THE CAR, RIGHT, SARAH?

15:39.109 --> 15:40.230
YEAH,
I THINK SO.

15:46.116 --> 15:47.277
[ GROANING ]

15:47.277 --> 15:50.240
SO, CHARLIE KISSED YOU
THIS MORNING.

15:50.240 --> 15:52.532
WAS THAT
YOUR FIRST KISS?

15:52.532 --> 15:56.206
YES. EXCEPT FOR THE GUY
WHO PLAYS SECOND-CHAIR CELLO.

15:56.206 --> 15:57.577
HE DOESN'T COUNT.

15:57.577 --> 15:58.708
[ Chuckling ] WHY?

15:58.708 --> 16:00.380
IT WAS JUST
PRACTICE KISSING.

16:00.380 --> 16:01.921
SO, SHOULD I
BE PRACTICING?

16:01.921 --> 16:04.004
NO.
YEAH,
BUT SHE JUST --

16:04.004 --> 16:06.046
BUT HOW MUCH TROUBLE
DO YOU THINK SHE'S GONNA BE IN

16:06.046 --> 16:08.258
WHEN HER MOTHER FINDS OUT
WHAT SHE'S BEEN UP TO TODAY?

16:08.258 --> 16:09.549
SHE HAS A POINT.

16:09.549 --> 16:11.431
I'M NOT
YOUR ROLE MODEL.

16:11.431 --> 16:14.894
I DON'T THINK KISSING CHARLIE
WAS WORTH ALL THIS.

16:14.894 --> 16:17.597
EVERY KISS BEFORE THE RIGHT KISS
DOESN'T COUNT ANYWAY.

16:17.597 --> 16:20.520
I'VE KISSED
A LOT OF WOMEN.

16:20.520 --> 16:24.194
THE FIRST TIME
I KISSED MY WIFE, WELL...

16:24.194 --> 16:27.157
I MEAN,
SHE WASN'T MY WIFE THEN.

16:27.157 --> 16:30.160
SHE WAS JUST
THIS GIRL IN A BAR.

16:30.160 --> 16:33.613
AND WHEN WE KISSED,
IT -- IT WAS LIKE...

16:33.613 --> 16:36.416
I GOT TO TELL YOU,
IT WAS LIKE

16:36.416 --> 16:38.038
I NEVER KISSED
ANY OTHER WOMAN BEFORE.

16:39.669 --> 16:42.082
IT WAS LIKE
THE FIRST KISS.

16:42.082 --> 16:43.673
THE RIGHT KISS.

16:43.673 --> 16:45.625
♪ THIS LAND BELONGS
TO THE GULLS ♪

16:45.625 --> 16:46.756
DO YOU HAVE
A BROTHER?

16:49.299 --> 16:51.471
♪ AND THE GULLS TO THEIR CRY ♪

16:51.471 --> 16:54.013
[ SIGHS ]

16:55.135 --> 16:56.476
♪ AND THEIR CRY TO THE WIND ♪

16:56.476 --> 16:58.848
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY
TO SAVE LIVES.

16:58.848 --> 17:00.900
WHAT --
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

17:00.900 --> 17:02.852
OH, IT'S JUST
A THING I SAY.

17:02.852 --> 17:04.234
OH.

17:04.234 --> 17:07.527
♪ AND THE WIND
BELONGS TO NO ONE ♪

17:07.527 --> 17:09.699
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

17:09.699 --> 17:11.741
DO YOU HEAR THAT?

17:11.741 --> 17:12.822
HEAR WHAT?

17:12.822 --> 17:14.824
[ WAILING CONTINUES ]
HEAR THAT?

17:14.824 --> 17:16.456
THEY GOT
OUR SMOKE SIGNAL!

17:16.456 --> 17:19.209
YEAH, THEY GOT
OUR SMOKE SIGNAL.
THEY GOT US!

17:19.209 --> 17:21.461
[ WAILING CONTINUES,
HORN BLARES ]

17:24.334 --> 17:27.297
[ INDISTINCT TALKING,
RADIO CHATTER ]

17:27.297 --> 17:33.093
♪ I'M CLIMBING
HAND OVER HAND ♪

17:33.093 --> 17:37.177
♪ TOWARD THAT PINPRICK
OF LIGHT ♪

17:37.177 --> 17:40.600
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

17:40.600 --> 17:41.941
I'LL VISIT YOU

17:41.941 --> 17:44.274
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING
AT THE HOSPITAL, OKAY?

17:44.274 --> 17:45.315
THANK YOU.

17:45.315 --> 17:47.487
OKAY,
WATCH YOUR STEP.

17:48.948 --> 17:51.951
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

17:51.951 --> 17:53.323
THANK YOU.

17:55.285 --> 18:00.370
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

18:00.370 --> 18:02.622
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

18:02.622 --> 18:05.205
GOT TO HAND IT
TO YOU, DOC.

18:05.205 --> 18:07.046
Firefighter: NOW GO
HOME AND HAVE YOURSELF
A DRINK. YOU EARNED IT.

18:07.046 --> 18:09.048
THANKS.

18:09.048 --> 18:12.262
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

18:12.262 --> 18:17.807
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

18:17.807 --> 18:23.102
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

18:23.102 --> 18:26.646
♪ OH, BABY ♪

18:26.646 --> 18:28.568
[ GRUNTS ]

18:28.568 --> 18:31.821
[ SIGHS ]
♪ TRY TO RECOGNIZE IT
IN MY MIND ♪

18:31.821 --> 18:35.034
♪ TRY TO STAMP IT OUT
BEFORE IT HAPPENS ♪

18:35.034 --> 18:36.196
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

18:38.618 --> 18:42.872
♪ I TRY TO RECOGNIZE IT
IN MY MIND ♪

18:42.872 --> 18:44.204
[ CELLPHONE BUZZING ]

18:44.204 --> 18:47.207
♪ TRY TO STAMP IT OUT ♪

18:47.207 --> 18:50.840
♪ TOWARD THE SEED
THAT GOD SOWED ♪

18:50.840 --> 18:51.841
[ HORN BLARES ]

18:51.841 --> 18:54.304
[ CRASH, TIRES SCREECHING ]

18:54.304 --> 18:56.886
SHE TOLD ME NOT TO WORRY.

18:56.886 --> 18:58.848
SHE TOLD ME
EVERYTHING WOULD BE FINE.

18:58.848 --> 19:03.563
[ SIREN WAILS, RADIO CHATTER ]
FUNNY, ISN'T IT,
THE WAY MEMORY WORKS?

19:03.563 --> 19:06.226
THE THINGS
YOU CAN'T QUITE REMEMBER...

19:06.226 --> 19:08.268
AND THE THINGS
YOU CAN NEVER FORGET.

19:08.268 --> 19:10.770
[ SIREN WAILING ]

19:10.770 --> 19:12.442
Owen: WHAT DO WE HAVE?
WHERE SHOULD I START?

19:12.442 --> 19:14.073
A BAD ONE. JEROME DAVIS.

19:14.073 --> 19:16.115
BLUNT-FORCE TRAUMA,
OPEN SKULL FRACTURE.

19:16.115 --> 19:18.037
HE KEEPS TRYING
TO DIE ON US.

19:18.037 --> 19:20.410
LET'S GET HIM INSIDE.
LET'S GO.

19:24.284 --> 19:25.995
NO, NO, NO,
WAIT.

19:25.995 --> 19:28.248
WHAT, NO!
ANOTHER ONE?!

19:28.248 --> 19:29.589
NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO.

19:29.589 --> 19:31.170
WE'VE ALREADY GOT THAT --
THAT LADY AND HER KID,

19:31.170 --> 19:32.252
THE -- THE GIRL
WITH THE GUTS,

19:32.252 --> 19:33.963
AND THEN THAT DUDE
WITH THE HEAD INJURY.

19:33.963 --> 19:35.094
WHEN IT RAINS,
IT POURS.

19:35.094 --> 19:36.846
OKAY,
IT NEEDS TO POUR SOMEWHERE ELSE

19:36.846 --> 19:38.558
BECAUSE WE ARE NOT
A TRAUMA CENTER.

19:38.558 --> 19:40.970
WE'RE NOT PROPERLY EQUIPPED
FOR THIS KIND OF THING.

19:40.970 --> 19:42.682
WE DON'T HAVE ROOMS.
YOU GUYS KNOW THAT.

19:42.682 --> 19:43.683
MAKE ROOM.

19:43.683 --> 19:46.145
WHAT ARE WE SUPPOSED TO DO
WITH THE GUY?

19:46.145 --> 19:47.397
LOOK AT HIM.

19:47.397 --> 19:49.479
[ SIGHS ]

19:49.479 --> 19:51.311
ALL RIGHT, FINE.
THIS ISN'T ON ME.

19:51.311 --> 19:54.404
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

20:00.910 --> 20:02.242
JOHN DOE BROADSIDED
BY A SEMI TRUCK.

20:02.242 --> 20:04.244
BLUNT-FORCE TRAUMA TO THE HEAD,
CHEST, AND ABDOMEN.

20:04.244 --> 20:07.126
PERSISTENT HYPOTENSION
AFTER TWO LITERS OF SALINE.

20:07.126 --> 20:08.498
PULSE IS THREADY
AT 130.

20:08.498 --> 20:10.880
Derek:
YOU'RE NOT DEAD.

20:10.880 --> 20:12.211
JUST BREATHE.

20:12.211 --> 20:13.092
I NEED
FOUR UNITS OF BLOOD.

20:13.092 --> 20:14.093
SCALP LAC.

20:14.093 --> 20:16.215
PROBABLY MULTIPLE FRACTURES.

20:16.215 --> 20:17.797
TRY TO HOLD STILL.

20:17.797 --> 20:20.720
JOHN DOE. BAD MVA.
HAD TO BE EXTRICATED.

20:20.720 --> 20:23.052
POSITIVE LOSS OF CONSCIOUSNESS
AT THE SCENE.

20:23.052 --> 20:24.053
HE'S POORLY RESPONSIVE.

20:24.053 --> 20:26.185
Toby: GCS OF 10.
WHAT'S YOUR NAME,
SIR?

20:26.185 --> 20:27.186
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

20:27.186 --> 20:29.769
YES. YES, I CAN HEAR YOU.

20:29.769 --> 20:32.061
LOSS OF VERBAL SKILLS.

20:32.061 --> 20:33.613
POSSIBLE BLEEDING IN THE BRAIN.

20:33.613 --> 20:35.194
HIS PUPILS
ARE EQUAL AND REACTIVE.

20:35.194 --> 20:37.156
GOOD SIGN.
STILL SHOULD GET A C.T.

20:37.156 --> 20:40.199
HE'S GOT A FLAIL CHEST
IN THE RIGHT. I NEED A
36 FRENCH TUBE NOW.

20:40.199 --> 20:41.491
SIR, CAN YOU TELL ME
YOUR NAME?

20:41.491 --> 20:44.033
HE'S STILL HYPOTENSIVE
AND TACHYCARDIC. UP TO
TWO FLUID BOLUSES.

20:44.033 --> 20:45.955
HE COULD BE BLEEDING
IN HIS CHEST.

20:45.955 --> 20:47.867
HANG TWO UNITS OF BLOOD
ON THE INFUSER.

20:47.867 --> 20:50.870
I NEED A TRAUMA PANEL AND X-RAY,
AND CROSS HIM FOR FOUR.

20:50.870 --> 20:52.752
AND SOMEBODY
PAGE SURGERY AGAIN.

20:52.752 --> 20:54.253
SHE'S SMART.
I LIKE HER.

20:54.253 --> 20:55.375
I'M SORRY.

20:55.375 --> 20:57.256
THIS IS GONNA HURT,
BUT WE HAVE TO DO IT.

20:57.256 --> 20:58.087
[ GASPS ]

21:04.554 --> 21:05.975
[ GASPS ]

21:09.689 --> 21:11.771
THAT MUST HAVE HURT.
I'M SORRY.

21:11.771 --> 21:13.983
CAN YOU PLEASE
TELL ME YOUR NAME?

21:13.983 --> 21:15.855
CAN YOU
TELL ME ANYTHING?

21:15.855 --> 21:18.358
[ MUTTERING ]

21:18.358 --> 21:22.071
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

21:22.071 --> 21:25.074
[ GROANS ]

21:32.872 --> 21:34.374
EXCUSE ME, TOBY?

21:49.689 --> 21:51.601
MOM, I'M GOING
TO THE BATHROOM.

21:51.601 --> 21:53.643
ASK A NURSE
WHERE IT IS.

21:53.643 --> 21:55.935
OW. YEAH.
RIGHT THERE.

21:58.027 --> 21:59.238
Edie:
I'M ORDERING A HEAD C.T.

21:59.238 --> 22:00.940
WE DON'T KNOW THE EXTENT
OF HIS HEAD INJURY.

22:00.940 --> 22:02.111
SHE'S RIGHT.

22:02.111 --> 22:04.153
YOU DON'T.

22:04.153 --> 22:05.284
Paul:
LOOK AT THE ULTRASOUND.

22:05.284 --> 22:06.866
HE'S BLEEDING
INTO HIS BELLY.

22:06.866 --> 22:08.157
WE DON'T HAVE TIME
FOR A C.T.

22:08.157 --> 22:09.038
ARROGANT --

22:09.038 --> 22:10.580
BECAUSE SHE'S YOUNGER THAN YOU

22:10.580 --> 22:12.412
AND PROBABLY
BECAUSE SHE'S A WOMAN.

22:12.412 --> 22:15.334
I JUST THINK THAT --
WE DON'T HAVE TIME FOR A C.T.

22:15.334 --> 22:17.046
HE NEEDS TO GO
STRAIGHT TO THE O.R.

22:17.046 --> 22:19.168
YOU HAVE THIS.
COME ON. DON'T BACK DOWN.

22:19.168 --> 22:20.720
I DON'T THINK WE HAVE A HANDLE
ON --

22:20.720 --> 22:23.222
HIS GCS HASN'T CHANGED
SINCE HE GOT HERE.

22:23.222 --> 22:24.464
THE C.T. CAN WAIT.

22:24.464 --> 22:27.637
Tech: C-SPINE, CHEST,
AND PELVIS FILMS ARE UP.

22:27.637 --> 22:29.639
[ CURTAIN RUSTLES ]

22:35.144 --> 22:36.275
DEREK?

22:39.939 --> 22:44.193
WINNIE.
YOU SHOULDN'T BE IN HERE.

22:45.405 --> 22:47.867
YOU'RE NOT DEAD.

22:49.619 --> 22:52.081
[ Voice breaking ]
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT DEAD.

22:52.081 --> 22:53.543
KNOW HOW I KNOW?

22:53.543 --> 22:56.295
'CAUSE I CAN FEEL
YOUR PULSE,

22:56.295 --> 22:58.047
WHICH MEANS YOUR HEART
IS BEATING.

22:58.047 --> 22:59.959
[ Crying ]
YOUR HEART IS BEATING,

22:59.959 --> 23:02.462
WHICH MEANS
YOU'RE NOT DEAD, OKAY?

23:06.175 --> 23:09.429
HEY.
EYES ON ME.

23:10.510 --> 23:13.352
YOU STAY NOT DEAD,
OKAY?

23:13.352 --> 23:17.066
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL DAY
TO SAVE LIVES, RIGHT?

23:17.066 --> 23:20.480
SO YOU STAY
NOT DEAD.

23:25.194 --> 23:27.116
Paul: WHERE ARE YOU
SUPPOSED TO BE?

23:27.116 --> 23:28.698
IS HE
GONNA BE ALL RIGHT?

23:29.789 --> 23:32.031
WHOSE KID IS THIS?

23:32.031 --> 23:34.033
I'LL DEAL WITH IT.

23:39.298 --> 23:42.672
I'M NOT DEAD.
I'M NOT DEAD.

23:42.672 --> 23:45.094
THAT MAN --
DO YOU KNOW HIM?

23:45.094 --> 23:46.425
YEAH,
THAT'S DEREK.

23:46.425 --> 23:48.598
DEREK? DEREK W-WHO?
IS HE A FAMILY MEMBER?

23:48.598 --> 23:49.599
A NEIGHBOR?

23:49.599 --> 23:50.930
HE'S MY FRIEND.

23:50.930 --> 23:51.931
OKAY.

23:51.931 --> 23:53.933
DO YOU KNOW
YOUR FRIEND'S LAST NAME?

23:53.933 --> 23:56.476
NO, I MEAN,
I JUST MET HIM TODAY.

23:56.476 --> 24:00.059
HE PULLED ME AND MY MOM OUT
OF OUR CAR AFTER THE ACCIDENT.

24:00.059 --> 24:02.612
HE FIXED HER LEG,
HE HELPED CHARLIE,

24:02.612 --> 24:05.064
AND HE PUT ALANA'S INSIDES
BACK IN.

24:05.064 --> 24:06.195
HE SAVED US.

24:06.195 --> 24:07.196
HE SAVED YOU?

24:07.196 --> 24:08.197
ALL OF US.

24:08.197 --> 24:10.369
HE'S A DOCTOR.

24:11.450 --> 24:13.282
HE'S A DOCTOR?

24:13.282 --> 24:15.625
A SURGEON,
I THINK.

24:15.625 --> 24:18.287
[ SLEEPING AT LAST'S
"TODAY HAS BEEN OKAY" PLAYS ]

24:20.379 --> 24:23.002
MY HEAD.
LOOK AT MY HEAD.

24:23.002 --> 24:25.044
[ MONITORS BEEPING ]
SEDATION, PLEASE!

24:25.044 --> 24:27.176
♪ FRIENDS TELL ME IT'S SPRING ♪

24:27.176 --> 24:29.388
YOU NEED TO CALM DOWN,
BUDDY.

24:29.388 --> 24:30.469
HE'S A SURGEON.

24:30.469 --> 24:33.222
LET'S GET A...

24:33.222 --> 24:36.095
HE'S A SURGEON,
AND HE JUST SAVED EVERYONE

24:36.095 --> 24:38.057
FROM THE CAR ACCIDENT
THAT JUST CAME THROUGH.

24:38.057 --> 24:40.399
♪ WITHOUT YOU HERE,
THE SEASONS PASS ME BY ♪

24:40.399 --> 24:42.151
DOCTOR,
WE'RE GONNA SEDATE YOU NOW

24:42.151 --> 24:43.563
SO WE CAN SECURE
YOUR AIRWAY.

24:43.563 --> 24:46.025
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.
NO. I'M NOT.

24:46.025 --> 24:47.156
YOU NEED TO WAIT.

24:49.238 --> 24:51.240
SUX AND ETOMIDATE IN?
YES.

24:51.240 --> 24:55.074
♪ I KNOW YOU WERE NOT NEW ♪

24:55.074 --> 24:57.076
IT'S OKAY.

24:57.076 --> 24:58.247
WE'VE GOT YOU.

24:58.247 --> 25:00.249
IT IS ALL
GONNA BE OKAY.

25:00.249 --> 25:02.582
THIS ISN'T RIGHT.

25:03.793 --> 25:07.466
YOU SHOULD HAVE TAKEN ME
TO GET A HEAD C.T.

25:09.889 --> 25:12.471
HIS PRESSURE'S HOLDING.
MAYBE WE SHOULD GET THE SCAN.

25:12.471 --> 25:14.513
YES, LISTEN TO HER.

25:14.513 --> 25:16.596
TOO RISKY. HE COULD BOTTOM
OUT IN THE SCANNER. WE
NEED TO OPEN HIM UP.

25:16.596 --> 25:17.767
FIND THE SOURCE
OF THE BLEEDING.

25:17.767 --> 25:19.478
NO, YOU DON'T.
YOU HAVE THE TIME.

25:19.478 --> 25:21.400
WE HAVE TO WORK FAST,
PEOPLE.
I'M STABLE.

25:21.400 --> 25:23.442
GUYS, I'M STABLE.

25:23.442 --> 25:25.695
TAKE ME TO GET THE HEAD C.T.

25:25.695 --> 25:27.026
LET'S SET UP
FOR AN EX-LAP.

25:27.026 --> 25:28.738
COMING THROUGH.

25:28.738 --> 25:31.821
I'M GOING TO DIE BECAUSE THESE
PEOPLE AREN'T PROPERLY TRAINED.

25:31.821 --> 25:35.204
♪ TODAY HAS BEEN OKAY ♪

25:39.538 --> 25:41.080
ONE, TWO, THREE.

25:41.080 --> 25:42.161
Paul:
HE'S HYPOTENSIVE.

25:42.161 --> 25:44.123
START HIM ON PRESSORS.
BETADINE.

25:44.123 --> 25:45.925
I CAN'T FEEL MY ARM.

25:45.925 --> 25:47.336
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

25:47.336 --> 25:49.128
READY TO PUT HIM UNDER.

25:49.128 --> 25:51.671
NO, I HAVE A HEAD LAC.

25:51.671 --> 25:54.053
DON'T MISS. DON'T MISS!

25:54.053 --> 25:55.514
THE COLON'S AVULSED.

25:55.514 --> 25:58.137
WE'LL NEED TO RESECT AND
CREATE A TEMPORARY COLOSTOMY.

25:58.137 --> 26:00.139
WELL, IT'S BETTER
THAN BEING DEAD, I GUESS.

26:00.139 --> 26:02.101
HE'S GOT
A GRADE-2 SPLENIC LAC.

26:02.101 --> 26:03.853
MEREDITH WOULD LEAVE IT.
Paul:
LET'S LEAVE IT.

26:03.853 --> 26:05.945
CHECK THE FOUR QUADRANTS.

26:05.945 --> 26:08.187
AND SHE'D DOUBLE CHECK
THE RETROHEPATIC SPACE.

26:08.187 --> 26:11.240
MAKE SURE TO CHECK
THE RETROHEPATIC SPACE.
NOT BAD.

26:11.240 --> 26:13.492
[ MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
CRAP. DROPPED HIS SATS.

26:14.784 --> 26:16.245
DECREASED BREATH SOUNDS
ON THE RIGHT.

26:16.245 --> 26:17.456
CHECK THE TEST TUBE.

26:17.456 --> 26:18.658
THE TEST TUBE
LOOKS GOOD.

26:18.658 --> 26:20.539
CHECK IT AGAIN.
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

26:22.201 --> 26:24.794
CRAP. HE'S GOT
A HUGE HEMOTHORAX.

26:24.794 --> 26:27.336
WE HAVE TO OPEN HIS CHEST.
THORACOTOMY TRAY.

26:27.336 --> 26:30.129
NO, DON'T. JUST WAIT.
SEE HOW MUCH BLOOD COMES OUT.

26:30.129 --> 26:32.011
IT'LL PROBABLY STOP.
JUST WAIT!

26:32.011 --> 26:33.342
SCALPEL.

26:36.555 --> 26:39.348
HE'S STILL HYPOTENSIVE.

26:39.348 --> 26:41.641
I CAN'T FIND
ANY LUNG LACERATION.

26:41.641 --> 26:43.643
HILUM'S INTACT.
HE'S NOT BLEEDING IN HIS CHEST.

26:43.643 --> 26:45.064
THIS MAKES NO SENSE.
WE'RE MISSING SOMETHING.

26:45.064 --> 26:46.435
SET UP FOR A T.E.E.

26:46.435 --> 26:48.067
NOT THAT.
THAT'S NOT WHAT YOU'RE MISSING.

26:48.067 --> 26:50.319
[ MONITORS BEEPING RAPIDLY ]
PERSISTENT BRADYCARDIA.

26:50.319 --> 26:51.651
CHECK MY HEAD.

26:51.651 --> 26:53.693
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT THE HELL IS...

26:53.693 --> 26:54.904
HE HAD
A HEAD LAC.

26:56.656 --> 26:58.367
CHECK HIS PUPILS.

26:58.367 --> 27:01.040
♪ COME ON,
PUT YOUR HANDS INTO THE FIRE ♪

27:01.040 --> 27:02.541
HIS RIGHT PUPIL
IS BLOWN.

27:02.541 --> 27:05.044
PAGE NEUROSURGERY
RIGHT FREAKING NOW.
WE DID.

27:05.044 --> 27:06.045
THEN PAGE THEM AGAIN.

27:06.045 --> 27:07.246
THEN PAGE THEM AGAIN.

27:07.246 --> 27:11.460
♪ AS I TURN, I MEET THE POWER ♪

27:11.460 --> 27:13.092
♪ THIS TIME, THIS TIME ♪

27:13.092 --> 27:14.343
[ DOOR OPENS ]
ANY WORD?

27:14.343 --> 27:16.015
THE NEUROSURGEON
WAS AT A DINNER.

27:16.015 --> 27:18.137
DINNER?

27:18.137 --> 27:19.218
DINNER?

27:19.218 --> 27:20.219
HE SAID HE'LL BE HERE
IN 20 MINUTES.

27:20.219 --> 27:21.310
IT WILL BE TOO LATE.

27:21.310 --> 27:22.311
♪ PULL UP ♪

27:22.311 --> 27:24.143
DAMN IT.

27:24.143 --> 27:26.645
♪ FROM ONE EXTREME TO ANOTHER ♪

27:26.645 --> 27:30.399
♪ FROM THE SUMMER
TO THE SPRING ♪

27:30.399 --> 27:33.943
♪ FROM THE MOUNTAIN
TO THE AIR ♪

27:33.943 --> 27:36.115
WHERE THE HELL
IS HE?

27:36.115 --> 27:37.656
PAGE HIM AGAIN.

27:41.330 --> 27:45.454
♪ FROM SAMARITAN TO SIN ♪

27:45.454 --> 27:53.632
♪ AND IT'S WAITING ON THE AIR ♪

27:53.632 --> 27:56.055
[ AIR HISSING ]

27:56.055 --> 27:59.138
♪ COME ON, COME ON ♪

27:59.138 --> 28:00.559
THANK GOD.

28:01.350 --> 28:03.352
WHAT THE HELL HAVE YOU PEOPLE
SCREWED UP NOW?

28:03.352 --> 28:04.764
US?

28:04.764 --> 28:06.856
YOU'RE ON CALL FOR TRAUMA.
WHAT TOOK YOU SO LONG?

28:06.856 --> 28:08.187
WHO THE HELL
ARE YOU?

28:08.187 --> 28:09.398
YOUR RESPONSE TIME
WAS SUPPOSED TO BE 20 MINUTES.

28:09.398 --> 28:11.480
IT WOULDN'T HAVE MADE
A DIFFERENCE.

28:11.480 --> 28:14.073
IF YOU GUYS HAD ORDERED
A HEAD C.T., YOU WOULD
HAVE CALLED ME SOONER.

28:14.073 --> 28:15.524
WHAT AM I
SUPPOSED TO DO ABOUT THAT?

28:15.524 --> 28:17.076
WE NEEDED
TO CONTROL.
HE WAS BLEEDING
INTO HIS BELLY.

28:17.076 --> 28:18.157
Dr. Cohn:
HE WAS STABLE.

28:18.157 --> 28:19.698
YOU HAD THE TIME.

28:19.698 --> 28:22.531
NOW I'VE GOT TO WORK LIKE HELL
TO SAVE THIS MAN, THANKS TO YOU.

28:23.492 --> 28:24.874
THERE'S NO POINT.

28:24.874 --> 28:27.787
YOU WERE SUPPOSED TO BE HERE
IN 20 MINUTES,

28:27.787 --> 28:29.248
NOT AN HOUR AND A HALF.

28:29.248 --> 28:32.131
WE HAD A CHANCE.
HE HAD A FREAKING CHANCE.

28:32.131 --> 28:33.712
GET OUT
OF MY O.R.

28:33.712 --> 28:35.004
WHAT?

28:35.004 --> 28:36.005
YOU HEARD ME.

28:36.005 --> 28:38.838
UNLESS YOU'RE GONNA BE CUTTING
INTO THIS MAN'S HEAD,

28:38.838 --> 28:39.889
YOU CAN GET OUT.

28:39.889 --> 28:41.180
NOW.

28:42.141 --> 28:44.603
NOW!

28:44.603 --> 28:46.185
♪ FROM SAMARITAN TO SIN ♪

28:46.185 --> 28:53.022
♪ AND IT'S WAITING ON THE AIR ♪

28:55.815 --> 28:57.276
I'M GONNA SCRUB IN.

28:57.276 --> 28:59.819
SOMEONE PULL IN
THE CRANIOTOMY TRAY.

28:59.819 --> 29:02.031
WE'VE ALREADY WASTED
ENOUGH TIME.

29:02.031 --> 29:04.954
IT'S TOO LATE.

29:04.954 --> 29:07.867
YOU'RE TOO LATE.

29:13.002 --> 29:15.214
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

29:20.009 --> 29:23.222
♪ FROM THE SUMMER
TO THE SPRING ♪

29:23.222 --> 29:28.267
♪ FROM THE MOUNTAIN TO THE AIR ♪

29:28.267 --> 29:31.150
HEY.

29:34.854 --> 29:37.196
WHAT DID YOU DO?

29:37.196 --> 29:39.068
OH, I DID
WHAT I ALWAYS DO,

29:39.068 --> 29:42.031
EXCEPT I ALMOST
KILLED MYSELF DOING IT.

29:42.031 --> 29:44.033
DON'T MAKE JOKES.

29:44.033 --> 29:45.614
I WAS SCARED.

29:45.614 --> 29:47.576
NO,
DON'T BE SCARED.

29:47.576 --> 29:49.909
I'M NOT
GOING ANYWHERE.

29:49.909 --> 29:51.620
♪ COME ON, COME ON ♪

29:51.620 --> 29:54.793
COME HERE.

29:54.793 --> 29:58.547
MM.
I'M RIGHT HERE.

29:58.547 --> 30:02.882
♪ COME ON, COME ON ♪

30:02.882 --> 30:04.884
Officer: MA'AM?

30:04.884 --> 30:07.096
MA'AM?

30:07.096 --> 30:08.687
MA'AM, IS THIS THE HOME
OF DEREK SHEPHERD?

30:08.687 --> 30:11.730
IT IS.
HE'S MY HUSBAND.

30:11.730 --> 30:16.065
I'M AFRAID
THERE'S BEEN AN ACCIDENT.

30:16.065 --> 30:17.646
COULD YOU COME WITH US,
PLEASE?

30:20.860 --> 30:22.071
ARE YOU OKAY?

30:22.071 --> 30:23.993
I C-- I-I CAN'T
JUST GO.

30:23.993 --> 30:27.366
I -- WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
WITH MY KIDS?

30:45.594 --> 30:47.846
Ellis: BLOOD.
IT'S JUST BLOOD.

30:51.310 --> 30:53.682
MEREDITH, DON'T BE AFRAID.

30:53.682 --> 30:55.144
DON'T BE AFRAI...

31:01.110 --> 31:04.323
[ Telephone dialing ]

31:04.323 --> 31:06.285
[ Ringing ]

31:06.285 --> 31:08.327
DISPATCHER: 911.
What's your emergency?

31:08.327 --> 31:09.989
Young Meredith: MY MOMMY
TRIED TO KILL HERSELF.

31:14.043 --> 31:16.045
Dr. Cohn: DR. GREY.

31:18.257 --> 31:20.629
DR. GREY, I CAN'T...

31:20.629 --> 31:24.173
WE CAN'T TELL YOU
HOW SORRY...

31:24.173 --> 31:27.676
I AM SO SORRY
FOR YOUR LOSS.

31:27.676 --> 31:32.101
DR. SHEPHERD
WAS A TREMENDOUS SURGEON --

31:32.101 --> 31:34.103
T-TREMENDOUSLY GIFTED.

31:34.103 --> 31:35.684
I'VE LONG ADMIRED
HIS TECHNIQUES.

31:35.684 --> 31:36.855
I...

31:36.855 --> 31:40.399
IT...
WAS AN HONOR.

32:03.842 --> 32:06.465
THE CALL TO NOT GET A HEAD C.T.
WAS A BAD CALL.

32:06.465 --> 32:07.716
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

32:07.716 --> 32:09.428
WE'RE NOT
A TRAUMA CENTER.

32:09.428 --> 32:11.140
WE'RE
A TEACHING HOSPITAL.

32:11.140 --> 32:13.973
YOU DID
THE BEST YOU COULD.

32:13.973 --> 32:17.936
[ RESPIRATOR HISSING,
MONITORS BEEPING ]

32:41.040 --> 32:42.631
MA'AM?

32:42.631 --> 32:45.504
I THOUGHT
THAT IF THIS WAS A GOOD TIME,

32:45.504 --> 32:49.138
I MIGHT TAKE A MOMENT TO EXPLAIN
HOW THIS ALL WORKS.

32:49.138 --> 32:50.679
WHERE ARE
THE PAPERS?

32:50.679 --> 32:53.722
MRS. SHEPHERD, THERE'S SOME
THINGS YOU NEED TO KNOW --

32:53.722 --> 32:55.594
SOME THINGS
WE NEED TO DISCUSS.

32:55.594 --> 32:56.805
DIFFICULT THINGS.

32:56.805 --> 33:00.649
I'M A DOCTOR.
DR. GREY.

33:00.649 --> 33:02.601
I'M A SURGEON,
JUST LIKE MY HUSBAND WAS.

33:02.601 --> 33:03.902
I KNOW
HOW THIS WORKS.

33:03.902 --> 33:06.065
YOU'VE WAITED
THE REQUISITE NUMBER OF HOURS,

33:06.065 --> 33:08.197
AND NOW YOU CAN
OFFICIALLY DECLARE HIM DEAD.

33:08.197 --> 33:10.319
NORMALLY, YOU'D TALK TO ME
ABOUT ORGAN DONATION.

33:10.319 --> 33:13.162
BUT BY THE LOOKS
OF HIS CHART,

33:13.162 --> 33:16.575
THERE'S NOT MUCH LEFT
THAT WORKS TO DONATE.

33:16.575 --> 33:19.168
SO,
THE I.C.U. NEEDS A BED.

33:19.168 --> 33:20.999
THOSE MUST BE
THE PAPERS --

33:20.999 --> 33:23.332
THE PAPERS
YOU WANT ME TO SIGN

33:23.332 --> 33:26.045
TO DECIDE WHAT TO DO
WITH MY HUSBAND...

33:26.045 --> 33:29.088
NOW THAT HE'S DEAD,
BUT NOT REALLY DEAD.

33:30.889 --> 33:33.092
DO WE SHIP HIM OFF
TO A LONG-TERM-CARE FACILITY

33:33.092 --> 33:37.186
AND CROSS OUR FINGERS AND
HOPE FOR FAIRY TALES AND MAGIC?

33:37.186 --> 33:39.138
OR DO I PULL THE PLUG?

33:39.138 --> 33:41.900
AND STOP
ALL CURATIVE INTERVENTION?

33:41.900 --> 33:44.733
DISCONTINUE
ALL ROUTINE MONITORING,

33:44.733 --> 33:47.816
REMOVE ALL THE CATHETERS,
DRAINS, AND TUBES,

33:47.816 --> 33:49.818
END ANY
AND ALL TREATMENTS

33:49.818 --> 33:52.741
THAT MIGHT PROVIDE COMFORT
TO THE PATIENT.

33:52.741 --> 33:57.116
TERMINATE ALL...

33:57.116 --> 33:59.458
LIFE-SUSTAINING MEASURES...

34:01.960 --> 34:06.085
...AND BEHAVE AS ANY SANE DOCTOR
WOULD BEHAVE.

34:08.757 --> 34:12.301
DOES THAT ABOUT COVER IT,
DOCTOR?

34:12.301 --> 34:16.095
[ Voice breaking ] IS THAT WHAT
YOU WANT TO TALK TO ME ABOUT...

34:16.095 --> 34:18.637
WHILE I SIT HERE
WITH MY SLEEPING CHILDREN?

34:18.637 --> 34:21.100
YOU WANT TO TALK
ABOUT KILLING MY HUSBAND?

34:21.100 --> 34:22.601
GIVE ME
THE PAPERS.

34:22.601 --> 34:24.273
MA'AM --

34:24.273 --> 34:25.644
GIVE ME THE PAPERS!

34:31.610 --> 34:35.454
[ SOBBING ]

34:36.905 --> 34:38.577
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

34:52.421 --> 34:55.304
[ Crying ]
I'M SO SORRY.

35:00.179 --> 35:02.641
I KNOW THAT
THAT'S USELESS TO YOU RIGHT NOW.

35:02.641 --> 35:04.483
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
BUT I AM.

35:04.483 --> 35:08.106
HE SAVED
ALL THOSE PEOPLE.

35:08.106 --> 35:12.110
AND IT WAS MY JOB...
TO SAVE HIM.

35:12.110 --> 35:14.112
AND I FAILED.

35:14.112 --> 35:17.536
AND NOW...
HE'S GONNA DIE...

35:17.536 --> 35:22.241
BECAUSE I WAS NOT
A GOOD ENOUGH DOCTOR...

35:22.241 --> 35:23.662
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

35:23.662 --> 35:26.044
...TO KEEP HIM ALIVE.

35:30.209 --> 35:32.301
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.
YOU DID FAIL.

35:32.301 --> 35:34.052
YOU WEREN'T
GOOD ENOUGH.

35:34.052 --> 35:37.055
BUT DO YOU KNOW
WHAT TOMORROW IS?

35:37.055 --> 35:38.257
IT'S FRIDAY.

35:38.257 --> 35:40.058
THERE'S GONNA BE MORE PATIENTS
WHO COME IN

35:40.058 --> 35:41.470
WHO NEED YOU
TO SAVE THEM --

35:41.470 --> 35:45.063
SOMEONE'S MOTHER, SOMEONE'S KID,
SOMEONE'S HUSBAND.

35:45.063 --> 35:46.265
THEY NEED YOU
TO SAVE THEM

35:46.265 --> 35:48.187
BECAUSE THEY CAN'T
SAVE THEMSELVES.

35:48.187 --> 35:51.650
SO LEARN FROM THIS,
BETTER YOURSELF,

35:51.650 --> 35:55.194
AND YOU WILL BE BETTER
FOR NEXT TIME.

35:55.194 --> 35:58.447
WHAT IF I'M NOT?

35:58.447 --> 36:00.199
YOU WILL BE.

36:00.199 --> 36:03.702
HOW CAN YOU KNOW THAT?

36:03.702 --> 36:06.084
BECAUSE HE
WAS YOUR ONE.

36:07.666 --> 36:09.167
EVERY PATIENT
YOU TREAT,

36:09.167 --> 36:11.089
YOU'RE GOING TO SEE
MY HUSBAND'S FACE

36:11.089 --> 36:15.173
AND REMEMBER THAT HE WAS THE ONE
THAT DIED ON YOUR WATCH.

36:17.676 --> 36:21.099
HE WILL HAUNT YOU.
THE HARD ONES ALWAYS DO.

36:21.099 --> 36:23.682
AND IT ONLY TAKES
THAT ONE.

36:23.682 --> 36:26.395
BUT THAT ONE
WILL MAKE YOU WORK HARDER,

36:26.395 --> 36:27.686
AND THEY MAKE YOU BETTER.

36:27.686 --> 36:29.768
OR THEY MAKE YOU QUIT,
AND YOU DON'T GET TO WASTE

36:29.768 --> 36:32.070
WHAT WOULD HAVE BEEN
THE REST OF MY HUSBAND'S LIFE

36:32.070 --> 36:33.071
BEING A QUITTER.

36:36.074 --> 36:37.316
SO GET BACK INSIDE

36:37.316 --> 36:39.908
BECAUSE YOU'RE NOT
SAVING ANY LIVES OUT HERE.

36:46.124 --> 36:47.165
I REALLY AM SO--

36:47.165 --> 36:49.918
YEAH, I KNOW.
I KNOW.

36:50.999 --> 36:54.172
[ SIGHS ]

36:58.887 --> 37:01.970
[ COUGHING ]

37:11.520 --> 37:13.562
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

37:38.427 --> 37:41.139
THERE'S A SOCIAL WORKER
OUT THERE WITH MY KIDS.

37:41.139 --> 37:42.471
IF THIS
TAKES A WHILE...

37:42.471 --> 37:43.882
WE GOT THEM.

37:43.882 --> 37:45.053
DON'T WORRY.

37:45.053 --> 37:48.096
I JUST NEED
THE PAPERS.

37:48.096 --> 37:50.689
[ RESPIRATOR HISSING,
MONITORS BEEPING ]

38:08.747 --> 38:10.539
WE'RE GONNA BEGIN NOW.

38:10.539 --> 38:13.211
YOU CAN SIT
NEXT TO HIM.

38:13.211 --> 38:16.915
[ "CHASING CARS" PLAYS ]

38:20.128 --> 38:23.181
♪ WE'LL DO IT ALL ♪

38:23.181 --> 38:24.633
[ BEEPING STOPS ]

38:24.633 --> 38:29.478
♪ EVERYTHING ♪

38:29.478 --> 38:32.270
♪ ON OUR OWN ♪

38:37.986 --> 38:40.569
♪ WE DON'T NEED ♪

38:42.491 --> 38:45.994
♪ ANYTHING ♪

38:45.994 --> 38:50.118
♪ OR ANYONE ♪

38:52.751 --> 38:54.663
♪ IF I LAY HERE ♪
WAIT.

38:54.663 --> 38:56.254
MA'AM --
JUST WAIT!

38:56.254 --> 39:01.049
♪ IF I JUST LAY HERE ♪

39:01.049 --> 39:07.175
♪ WOULD YOU LIE WITH ME
AND JUST FORGET THE WORLD? ♪

39:07.175 --> 39:09.177
DEREK.

39:13.021 --> 39:15.894
♪ I DON'T QUITE KNOW ♪

39:15.894 --> 39:17.936
DEREK.

39:17.936 --> 39:20.148
♪ HOW TO SAY ♪
Derek: SO,
WHAT'S YOUR STORY?

39:20.148 --> 39:22.981
I DON'T HAVE A STORY.
I'M JUST A GIRL IN A BAR.

39:22.981 --> 39:25.363
♪ HOW I FEEL ♪
I'M JUST
A GUY IN A BAR.

39:25.363 --> 39:26.615
WANT TO GO AGAIN?

39:26.615 --> 39:28.867
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

39:28.867 --> 39:31.329
I LOVE YOU,
MEREDITH GREY.

39:31.329 --> 39:35.624
♪ THOSE THREE WORDS ♪
AND I WANT TO SPEND
THE REST OF MY LIFE WITH YOU.

39:35.624 --> 39:37.706
♪ ARE SAID TOO MUCH ♪
Derek: YOU'RE THE LOVE
OF MY LIFE.

39:37.706 --> 39:39.958
I CAN'T LEAVE YOU.

39:39.958 --> 39:42.210
♪ THEY'RE NOT ENOUGH ♪

39:42.210 --> 39:45.554
YOU WERE LIKE COMING UP
FOR FRESH AIR.

39:45.554 --> 39:47.846
♪ AND IF I LAY HERE ♪
IT'S LIKE I WAS DROWNING,
AND YOU SAVED ME.

39:49.347 --> 39:52.681
♪ IF I JUST LAY HERE ♪
I'M IN LOVE WITH YOU.

39:54.102 --> 39:58.146
♪ WOULD YOU LIE WITH ME ♪
I'VE BEEN IN LOVE WITH YOU
FOREVER.

39:58.146 --> 40:01.980
♪ AND JUST FORGET THE WORLD? ♪

40:01.980 --> 40:07.155
♪ FORGET WHAT WE'RE TOLD ♪
SO, UM, GOODBYE.

40:07.155 --> 40:09.528
♪ BEFORE WE GET TOO OLD ♪
UM...

40:09.528 --> 40:10.989
DEREK.

40:10.989 --> 40:12.701
DEREK.

40:12.701 --> 40:14.122
♪ SHOW ME A GARDEN ♪
RIGHT. MEREDITH.

40:14.122 --> 40:15.413
MEREDITH.
YEAH.

40:15.413 --> 40:17.125
♪ THAT'S BURSTING INTO LIFE ♪
MM-HMM.

40:17.125 --> 40:20.539
